race.comment: OUR QUEEN (4) made it three wins from just four starts when she easily disposed of a field of similar quality last start over 1250m at Canterbury. Tried once at this trip and got the prize at Sandown. Is being handled patiently by the Baker camp. Should be winning better races so another BM72 looks to be hers for the taking. WINSTON HILLS (3) has been knocking on the door. Back a little in grade today but does get 60kgs to compensate. Each-way prospect. THE REPLICANT (7) caught the eye over 1300m here last start and will enjoy this slightly longer journey. DIVINE BENE (10) has been freshened since placing at Randwick. Will go forward from the low gate and take catching.
